  "body": "## Summary\nThis PR addresses all code review comments from Gemini Code Assist for the \"Feat/editable feed urls fixed\" feature.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### Backend Performance Optimization\n- Fixed performance issue in `update_feed_url` function by replacing redundant `fetch_and_update_feed` call with direct `process_feed_entries` to avoid duplicate network requests\n\n### Frontend Configuration\n- Updated API configuration to use relative paths for production deployment instead of hardcoded port 5001\n\n### Frontend Error Handling\n- Fixed syntax error in `handleEditFeedSubmit` function\n- Improved user experience in edit modal with proper error handling\n\n### Testing\n- Updated test to match optimized implementation\n- All tests passing (74 passed, 1 skipped)\n\n## Technical Details\n- Backend: Modified `update_feed_url` to use `process_feed_entries` directly instead of calling `fetch_and_update_feed` again\n- Frontend: Updated API_BASE_URL configuration for production compatibility\n- Documentation: Updated CHANGELOG.md and TODO.md\n\n## Verification\n- All three identified code review issues resolved\n- Backend performance optimized by eliminating redundant network calls\n- Frontend API configuration fixed for production deployment\n- Error handling UX improved with proper syntax and user feedback\n\nThis addresses the feedback from the previous PR #100 review cycle.",

arguments.body:
## Summary
This PR addresses the remaining code review comments from Gemini Code Assist for the "Feat/editable feed urls fixed" feature.

## Changes Made

### Backend Test Optimization
- Removed unused `@patch('backend.app.fetch_and_update_feed')` decorator and `mock_fetch_and_update` argument from `test_update_feed_url_success` test
- The test now only mocks `fetch_feed` since the optimized implementation uses `process_feed_entries` directly

### Frontend Error Handling
- Simplified `handleEditFeedSubmit` function by removing unreachable else block
- Cleaned up error handling to directly use `error.message` for cleaner display

## Technical Details
- Backend: Test now matches the optimized implementation that avoids redundant network calls
- Frontend: Improved user experience with proper error handling and loading states

## Verification
- All tests passing (74 passed, 1 skipped)
- Backend performance optimized by eliminating duplicate network requests
- Frontend error handling improved with cleaner syntax and user feedback

This completes the code review cycle for the editable feed URLs feature.
